{
  "text": "Cymothoid species using 16s rDNA and COI gene recommended that Cymothoids may have originated in deep seas, then diffused to shallow seas, and then to brackish or freshwater [CITATION_1] . Host specificity and host range vary among. In general, however, cymothoids that attach to external surfaces of fish display wider host ranges than other species, sometimes mount fish orders [CITATION_2] . Several molecular phylogenetic studies on the family Cymothoidae, the reference frameworks are imprecise; vague sequences were included in previous phylogenies based on 16S rRNA and COI sequences [CITATION_3] . Cymothoids that are parasitic in the buccal cavities show average distance accross host range ",
